8d396d36-2f1a-4c43-8c20-d5f29e164632.00d6e448-9b49-4770-8930-83444fd4b9c4.description=
Executes an Expression (e.x value1 \=\= value2)

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the value to threshold with
value2 - the threshold to threshold against
operator - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
okstring - string to push into returnResult if the threshold has not been passed
failedstring - string to push into the returnResult if the threshold has been passed

Responses\:
true - the expression is true
fales - the expression is false
8d396d36-2f1a-4c43-8c20-d5f29e164632.0f4bba38-f62d-448f-b42a-e71b7fbdf813.description= 
Compares a files size to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
source - the file to read
Threshold - the threshold to compare the file size to (in bytes).
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's size is larger than the threshold.
less than		- The file's size is smaller than the threshold.
equal to		- The file's size is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
size			- The file's size in bytes.
8d396d36-2f1a-4c43-8c20-d5f29e164632.310f8c55-0d4e-4eb3-a5ba-3707e72042ff.description=
Adds a value into the global context (available to all parent and child flows)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
8d396d36-2f1a-4c43-8c20-d5f29e164632.4686573c-f294-4cdd-9aa9-50d06520ca86.prompt=Should the operation check subfolders? WARNING this may be very slow 8d396d36-2f1a-4c43-8c20-d5f29e164632.a123489f-f557-437d-8b85-ada186d6eae4.description= 
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.
8d396d36-2f1a-4c43-8c20-d5f29e164632.description=
Goes through a windows directory and returns the largest file.

Inputs\:
Source - The source directory.
user - the username to run as.
password - password for user.
recursive - whether to recurse through sub directories.

Responses\:
success - operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.

8d396d36-2f1a-4c43-8c20-d5f29e164632.f5efb03d-881e-4953-8ab6-6cfadc552dfa.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration..
flow.name: Get Largest File
